==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Congo red
<hw>Congo red</hw>. <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>An artificial red dye from
which the Congo group received its name. It is also widely used either
in aqueous solution or as test paper (<col><b>Congo paper</b></col>) for
the detection of free acid, which turns it blue.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Congo snake</ent>⟦br⟧
